### HEALTH CHECK ###

### Health check
GET http://localhost:5001/health

### AUTHENTICATION ###

### Register a new user
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "name": "John Doe"
}

### Register with duplicate email (expect 409)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "name": "John Doe Again"
}

### Register with missing name (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bad@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Register with short password (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "short@example.com",
  "password": "123",
  "name": "Short"
}

### Register with unknown field (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "name": "Test",
  "role": "admin"
}

### Register with invalid email (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "password": "password123",
  "name": "Bad Email"
}

### Login
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login wrong password (expect 401)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### Login non-existent email (expect 401)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nonexistent@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login with missing fields (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Create a second user (for cross-user tests)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "name": "Jane Doe"
}

### Login as second user
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### TASKS (Requires Bearer Token) ###
### =================================
### IMPORTANT: Replace {{authToken}} below with a real token from the Login response above.
### In VS Code REST Client you can use @variableName for this. But for simplicity,
### copy the token from the login response and paste it below directly.
### =================================

### Set auth token variable (paste your token here)
@authToken = <your_jwt_token_here>

### Create a task
POST http://localhost:5001/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Complete project report",
  "description": "Write the quarterly project report for stakeholders"
}

### Create task without description
POST http://localhost:5001/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Buy groceries"
}

### Create task with empty title (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": ""
}

### Create task with unknown field (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Test",
  "unknownField": "should fail"
}

### Get all tasks
GET http://localhost:5001/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get task by ID (replace with actual ID)
@taskId = <replace_with_task_id>
GET http://localhost:5001/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get task with invalid UUID (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:5001/api/tasks/not-a-uuid
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get task that does not exist (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:5001/api/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Update task (replace with actual ID)
PATCH http://localhost:5001/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Updated project report",
  "isCompleted": true
}

### Update task with empty body (expect 400)
PATCH http://localhost:5001/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{}

### Update task with unknown field (expect 400)
PATCH http://localhost:5001/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Test",
  "unknownField": "should fail"
}

### Delete task (replace with actual ID)
DELETE http://localhost:5001/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Delete task that does not exist (expect 404)
DELETE http://localhost:5001/api/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### AUTH GUARD TESTS ###

### Access tasks without token (expect 401)
GET http://localhost:5001/api/tasks

### Access tasks with invalid token (expect 401)
GET http://localhost:5001/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here

### CROSS-OWNERSHIP TESTS ###
### These require two valid tokens from two different users.
### Run these after getting a task ID from user 1.

### Try to access user 1's task as user 2 (expect 403)
### Replace {{user2Token}} and {{user1TaskId}}
@user2Token = <user2_jwt_token>
@user1TaskId = <task_id_belonging_to_user1>
GET http://localhost:5001/api/tasks/{{user1TaskId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{user2Token}}

### Try to update user 1's task as user 2 (expect 403)
PATCH http://localhost:5001/api/tasks/{{user1TaskId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{user2Token}}

{
  "title": "Hacked!"
}

### Try to delete user 1's task as user 2 (expect 403)
DELETE http://localhost:5001/api/tasks/{{user1TaskId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{user2Token}}
